cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.EM, cs.MS, cs.SY

The paper discusses the implementation of a stochastic neuron using an insulator-metal-transition (IMT) device, which is relevant to the fields of neuromorphic engineering (cs.NE), electronic devices (cs.ET), materials science (cs.EM), control systems (cs.SY), and statistical modeling (cs.MS). The focus on stochasticity and noise in the device also suggests a potential fit for the cs.ST sub-category, but this is less likely given the specific emphasis on IMT devices and their application to neural networks.
